abstract: It’s one of the largest such settlements ever, shining additional light on what some advocates see as racial disparities in the case, in which the victim was white and the officer was black.

abstract: Inspired by Jerome Robbins, who cast him in the stage and film versions of “West Side Story,” he went on to create dances for Ann-Margret and others.
snippet: Inspired by Jerome Robbins, who cast him in the stage and film versions of “West Side Story,” he went on to create dances for Ann-Margret and others.
lead_paragraph: David Winters, who danced in the original Broadway production of “West Side Story” and then fashioned an influential if under-the-radar show business career, notably as a choreographer for Ann-Margret, Elvis Presley and others, died on April 23 in Fort Lauderdale, Fla. He was 80.

abstract: James Bennet, the chief of the newspaper’s Opinion section, said he would separate himself from any work related to the presidential election.
snippet: James Bennet, the chief of the newspaper’s Opinion section, said he would separate himself from any work related to the presidential election.
lead_paragraph: James Bennet, the editorial page editor of The New York Times, said on Thursday that he would recuse himself from any involvement in opinion coverage of the 2020 presidential election, after his brother, Senator Michael Bennet of Colorado, announced his candidacy for the Democratic nomination.

abstract: Seventeen candidates have already qualified for the first debate. Here is a look at how the party will decide who makes the stage if that number passes 20.
snippet: Seventeen candidates have already qualified for the first debate. Here is a look at how the party will decide who makes the stage if that number passes 20.
lead_paragraph: During the 2016 presidential primary, leaders of the Democratic National Committee were frequently accused of showing favoritism toward Hillary Clinton over Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont. Perhaps as a result, party officials have tried to make the 2020 primary process appear more inclusive and transparent.

abstract: Mr. Bennet, a moderate Democrat from Colorado, has been involved in bipartisan Senate compromises on immigration, education and other issues.
snippet: Mr. Bennet, a moderate Democrat from Colorado, has been involved in bipartisan Senate compromises on immigration, education and other issues.
lead_paragraph: Senator Michael Bennet of Colorado, the 21st Democrat to declare his candidacy for president, is known as a moderate who seeks bipartisan compromise. Here’s where he stands on a few key issues.

headline_main: Where Michael Bennet Stands on the Issues

abstract: The moderate senator joins a Democratic field so crowded with candidates that it now includes six of his Senate colleagues and his former boss.
snippet: The moderate senator joins a Democratic field so crowded with candidates that it now includes six of his Senate colleagues and his former boss.
lead_paragraph: DENVER — Michael Bennet, the moderate, studious Democratic senator from Colorado known for his work on education and immigration reform, announced his candidacy for president on Thursday.
